sql:
SELECT AVG(T1.income_level) AS average_income_level
FROM income AS T1
JOIN risk_scores AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id;

external_knowledge:
- A risk score of '0.8' might signify a high risk; 
- The '0.8' risk score threshold might be a critical value for account monitoring or review; 
- Predictions are considered on the basis of the most recent prediction date; 
- Active accounts are those that are currently in use.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.customer_id) AS customer_count, SUM(CAST(T2.income_level AS REAL)) AS total_income
FROM customers AS T1
JOIN income AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id;

